Ecological notes . The specimens were collected at the Córrego do Arajara, a small stream in the peri-urban region of the Arajara district. The stream has deforested margins surrounded by farms and corrals and is located in a slope area of pluvio-nebular forest, evergreen, about 750 m above sea level, with representatives from the Atlantic and Amazonian forests (
Sales et al. 1998
). The stream was shallower than 1 m and 4 to 5 m wide, perennial, and with medium energy, with bottoms of consolidated sandstone blocks and clear water ( Fig. 5A ). The specimens were found between rocks and in small crevices of about 20 to 50 cm deep ( Fig. 5B ). Burrows were not found on the margins or in the riverbed. Crabs were more active at night and were probably hiding and inactive during the day.
